commit_list.message:
ratom patch

Hello,

I've been using your ratom gem to parse data from some of the google
apis.  One bug I've noticed is when there is xml data in
simple_exensions, all of the xml tags are stripped out.  This is a
simple fix and I've attached a patch.

Thanks,

-min
From c8a34c77f49a3a34ef4ae262acf04b7877bbe074 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Min Kim <minho.kim@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Jun 2008 21:52:59 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] allow simple_extensions to have xml content

---
 lib/atom/xml/parser.rb                          |    2 +-
 spec/atom_spec.rb                               |    4 ++++
 spec/fixtures/entry_with_simple_extensions.atom |    3 ++-
 3 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

Signed-off-by: Sean Geoghegan <seangeo@gmail.com>
